This is a 2D Lunar Lander game written using Python and PyGame.  You can use the left and right arrow keys to turn, and space to thrust.  The objective of the game is to land as softly as possible on the landing pad.

This software is based on the LunarLander sample program from the book Hello World! Computer Programming for Kids and Other Beginners.  That software is © Warren Sande, 2009.  It is released under the MIT license, which can be found at http://www.opensource.org/licenses/mit-license.php